[[SECTION]]
MID: 2b92467cbac849779086bee79203eb9b
TITLE: WP planning

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: 939110c1bf94440dbcac626cf18c63ef
UID: SDOC-LLR-206
STATUS: Active
TITLE: EPIC node structure
STATEMENT: >>>
The ``[EPIC]`` node structure shall be as follows:

- MID
- UID
- STATUS
- ASSIGNED_PERSON
- ASSIGNED_TEAM
- TIME_START
- TIME_END
- TITLE
- STATEMENT

The format for status shall be Ready, WIP, Done, Draft. The corresponding colors shall be derived from this status field and used in the web interface.

The format for time fields shall be ISO 8601, e.g., ``2026-03-28T16:28:02Z``.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: 543c257fc6404d52861f7e3230a7b2b7
UID: SDOC-LLR-208
STATUS: Active
TITLE: EPIC node display rules
STATEMENT: >>>
The ``[EPIC]`` node shall be displayed on the Planning Canvas according to the following rules:

- When an epic node has its time start and time end fields populated, it shall be displayed on the Planning Canvas. Otherwise, it shall stay in the Backlog section next/to the left of the Planning Canvas.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: f2df4d1d92d544638cc659ea74da0673
UID: SDOC-LLR-207
STATUS: Active
TITLE: WORK_PACKAGE node structure
STATEMENT: >>>
The ``[WORK_PACKAGE]`` node structure shall be as follows:

- MID
- UID
- TITLE
- STATEMENT

NOTE: The work package does not have its own duration, its duration is formed by the durations of the epic that it contains.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: 4433d685c487437fac6948d6e03f47c6
UID: SDOC-LLR-209
STATUS: Active
TITLE: WORK_PACKAGE node moving rules (drag-and-drop)
STATEMENT: >>>
When a ``[WORK_PACKAGE]`` node is dragged on the Planning Canvas, the Planning Canvas shall move the entire work package node, updating all its contained epic time-start and time-end fields accordingly and preserving the overall duration of all epics.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: 727f8680aa85498e93c30a0c8d3580d1
UID: SDOC-LLR-210
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Panning behavior
STATEMENT: >>>
When Space key is pressed, the Planning Canvas component shall support panning both horizontally and vertically.

NOTE: The panning behavior shall still be active after any editing and AJAX updates take place.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[REQUIREMENT]
MID: a4b0e87a096141838ba162cd862c4c77
UID: SDOC-LLR-211
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Layout rules for EPIC nodes
STATEMENT: >>>
Work Planner shall allocate EPIC nodes on the Planning Canvas as follows:

- The nodes must never overlap visually, neither vertically or horizontally.
- If two nodes overlap in time, they shall be placed on two different vertical levels.
- The algorithm shall optimize for a number of levels. See optimization examples below.

Optimization examples:

1) When a node A overlaps with node B and node B overlaps with node C but A and C don't overlap, then A and C shall be placed to the same level and the node B shall be placed to the level below.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SDOC-SRS-205

[[/SECTION]]
